Ban said on Wednesday at a conference that he plans to meet with foreign ministers from five countries permanently present on the council - the US, Russia, China, England and France - on the sidelines of the General Assembly's ministerial session to discuss Syria.
Ban regretted that divisions in the council and between the Syrian people and regional powers "made this situation unsolvable."
Ban urged the five permanent members to show solidarity and unity when they were able to conclude an agreement on Iran's nuclear weapons, thus addressing the crisis in Syria.
