The rare illness a man suffers from
The American Nick Hess was suspected by his family of being an alcoholic, his wife even filming him when he was dizzy, he could barely stand up and his words were hard to understand.
Although the 35-year-old said he didn't drink alcohol, it was visible that he was intoxicated.
When she first accused me of being drunk without drinking, I thought she was crazy.
"But friends and family believed 'maybe he drank on his own, he's a secret alcoholic'," he tells the story, according to Mirror.
When he saw his wife's footage of him, the man from Columbus, Ohio, he just didn't recognize himself, "I was looking into my eyes and I wasn't there."
'It was awful, I didn't remember anything. '
Besides, his wife, who, although she doubted him for a while, finally went with him to countless doctors, remembers that Nick's breath smelled like alcohol.
The moment that got Nick thinking the most was when, after a minor accident, when he was hit by another car, it was discovered that he had an alcohol level three times over his legal limit, although the night before, he had only consumed one beer.
After years and endless investigations, it was discovered that Nick suffers from an extremely rare disease, "Auto-brewery syndrome."
Basically, his body makes all the carbohydrates consumed ferment, turning into alcohol.
The one who suspected that this might be Nick's illness was even his wife.
The disease doesn't have a cure yet, but since it dropped carbs, Nick hasn't had one of these episodes.
